# Main/Play.elm — EARLY

Embeddable Play component. Owns the live-play lifecycle —
init / update / view / subscriptions — of a LynRummy session.
The main app (`Main.elm`) wraps one Play instance in a
viewport-filling shell; the Puzzles gallery (`Puzzles.elm`)
embeds many Play instances side-by-side as gallery panels.

Extracted from the pre-split `Main.elm` on 2026-04-23 as
REFACTOR_EMBEDDABLE_PLAY phases I-III.

## Public API

```elm
type Config
    = NewSession
    | ResumeSession Int
    | PuzzleSession Int

type Output
    = NoOutput
    | SessionChanged Int

init : Config -> (Model, Cmd Msg)
update : Msg -> Model -> (Model, Cmd Msg, Output)
view : Model -> Html Msg
subscriptions : Model -> Sub Msg
```

`Model` and `Msg` are re-exports of `Main.State.Model` /
`Main.Msg.Msg` — NOT opaque yet. Hosts can inspect/read them.
Opaqueness is a later phase once we've validated that no host
legitimately needs that access.

## Config

- `NewSession` — fire `fetchNewSession`; server allocates an
  id. Main app's default landing page.
- `ResumeSession sid` — fetch action log for `sid`. Main
  app's URL-resume path.
- `PuzzleSession { sessionId, puzzleName, initialState }` —
  synchronous bootstrap from the catalog payload. No HTTP. The
  Puzzles gallery calls this for every puzzle on catalog
  landing; the page-load session_id (allocated by the catalog
  endpoint at GET time) is shared across every panel;
  puzzleName tags wire writes so they land in
  `lynrummy_elm_puzzle_actions`.

## Output

The host reacts to `SessionChanged sid` by pinning the URL
path (main app) or caching the id per panel (Puzzles
gallery). `NoOutput` covers every other update.

## Depends on

All of the Main/* support modules it always has:

- `Main.State` — Model type, baseModel, `boardDomIdFor`.
- `Main.Msg` — Msg type.
- `Main.Apply` — reducer (`applyAction`).
- `Main.Gesture` — drag start/end, `fetchBoardRect`.
- `Main.Wire` — HTTP.
- `Main.View` — the embeddable game-surface render.
- `Game.Replay.Time` — replay FSM.

## Stays in Main.elm (harness)

- `port setSessionPath` — only port modules may declare ports.
  Main.elm fires it when Play emits `SessionChanged`.
- `Browser.element` boot.
- The viewport-filling outer shell (the main app looks
  full-page; Puzzles gallery panels don't).

